{"parse":{"title":"Flaggers (Confederate flag erectors)","pageid":57972292,"revid":860025160,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Flaggers are one of the several pro-<a href=\"/wiki/Confederate_States_of_America\" title=\"Confederate States of America\">Confederacy</a> groups that operate openly in the United States (as of 2018). The best-known others are the <a href=\"/wiki/Sons_of_Confederate_Veterans\" title=\"Sons of Confederate Veterans\">Sons of Confederate Veterans</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/United_Daughters_of_the_Confederacy\" title=\"United Daughters of the Confederacy\">United Daughters of the Confederacy</a>.\n</p><p>Flaggers usually operate at the state level. Their primary purpose is to make the <a href=\"/wiki/Modern_display_of_the_Confederate_flag#The_vernacular_&quot;Confederate_flag&quot;\" title=\"Modern display of the Confederate flag\">Confederate battle flag</a> as visible as possible. They carry it at demonstrations and other public events, and erect it on private land. These flags are frequently visible from major highways, and have often been the subject of controversy and legal efforts to have them removed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-ignore_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ignore-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-washposttheterrifyingconfederatestatue_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-washposttheterrifyingconfederatestatue-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> They (as individuals) lobby or appear at meetings to speak against <a href=\"/wiki/Removal_of_Confederate_monuments_and_memorials\" title=\"Removal of Confederate monuments and memorials\">removal of Confederate monuments and memorials</a>. They are anti-<a href=\"/wiki/Abraham_Lincoln\" title=\"Abraham Lincoln\">Abraham Lincoln</a> and for the right of states to secede, i.e., that the Confederacy was legitimate under U.S. law.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> See <a href=\"/wiki/Lost_Cause_of_the_Confederacy\" title=\"Lost Cause of the Confederacy\">Lost Cause of the Confederacy</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Georgia_origin_of_flaggers\">Georgia origin of flaggers</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Flaggers_(Confederate_flag_erectors)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Georgia origin of flaggers\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The earliest documentation of a flagger group as an organization is the Virginia Flaggers, whose Web site says they were founded in 2011. However, the flagger movement first appeared, spontaneously and unorganized, in Georgia in 2001.\n</p><p>The flag of Georgia from 1956 to 2001 incorporated the Confederate battle flag. Responding in part to pressure from civil rights groups who threatened an economic boycott of Georgia, African-American Governor <a href=\"/wiki/Roy_Barnes\" title=\"Roy Barnes\">Roy Barnes</a> \"ramrodded\" a flag change bill through the Legislature.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Savannah_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Savannah-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The new, hastily-designed flag, which even many of its supporters thought ugly,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Savannah_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Savannah-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> was in use from 2001 to 2003. The <a href=\"/wiki/North_American_Vexillological_Association\" title=\"North American Vexillological Association\">North American Vexillological Association</a> called it the worst-designed state flag in the country.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Encyclopedia_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Encyclopedia-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> It included the Confederate battle flag as just one of five flags that have flown over Georgia.\n</p><p>There was widespread opposition to the new flag, deemed the \"Barnes flag\". It led, according to Barnes himself, to his defeat for reelection two years later; the flag was a major issue in the election.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Savannah_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Savannah-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> A new flag was designed. In a non-binding 2004 referendum, 73% of the voters expressed a preference for the new flag, based on the <a href=\"/wiki/Flags_of_the_Confederate_States_of_America#First_flag:_the_&quot;Stars_and_Bars&quot;_(1861\u20131863)\" title=\"Flags of the Confederate States of America\">First Confederate national flag</a>, the Stars and Bars, over the 2001 design. (A return to the 1956 flag with the Confederate battle flag, desired by some, was not on the ballot.)\n</p><p>Flaggers, as they were soon called,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Encyclopedia_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Encyclopedia-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> began displaying the Confederate battle flag, or the 1956 Georgia flag which contained it, in 2001. They appeared at political rallies and at public appearances of legislators who had voted for the Barnes flag. An undated video showing a parade of the day, with flaggers and a lesser number of supporters of the Barnes flag, Is available on <a href=\"/wiki/YouTube\" title=\"YouTube\">YouTube</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Current_flagger_groups\">Current flagger groups</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Flaggers_(Confederate_flag_erectors)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Current flagger groups\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>As of 2018, the active flagger groups are:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Virginia Flaggers, according to <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://vaflaggers.blogspot.com\">their Web site</a>, formed in 2011. They have installed Confederate flags across the state.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> It was they who, according to the credits, posted the YouTube video cited.</li>\n<li>Tennessee Confederate Flaggers<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Alabama Flaggers<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Delta (Mississippi) Flaggers, who make a point of demonstrating in front of businesses, schools, or any organization that does not fly the <a href=\"/wiki/Mississippi_Flag\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mississippi Flag\">Mississippi Flag</a> (which contains the <a href=\"/wiki/Confederate_Battle_Flag\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Confederate Battle Flag\">Confederate Battle Flag</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Georgia Flaggers<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bearden_at_Alpharetta_Aug_2018.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Bearden_at_Alpharetta_Aug_2018.jpg/220px-Bearden_at_Alpharetta_Aug_2018.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"261\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Bearden_at_Alpharetta_Aug_2018.jpg/330px-Bearden_at_Alpharetta_Aug_2018.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Bearden_at_Alpharetta_Aug_2018.jpg/440px-Bearden_at_Alpharetta_Aug_2018.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2351\" data-file-height=\"2792\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Bearden_at_Alpharetta_Aug_2018.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Georgia Flagger with large flag on 20 foot pole at Alpharetta Old Soldiers' Parade, Alpharetta, Georgia on 4 August 2018.</div></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Flaggers_(Confederate_flag_erectors)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Basham, Marc (July 22, 2018). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://idahostatejournal.com/news/local/east-idaho-confederate-flag-display-creates-controversy/article_659c7ac7-37c1-5ad9-a996-a243868b3207.html\">\"East Idaho Confederate flag display creates controversy\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Idaho_Statesman\" title=\"Idaho Statesman\">Idaho Journal Statesman</a></i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Idaho+Journal+Statesman&amp;rft.atitle=East+Idaho+Confederate+flag+display+creates+controversy&amp;rft.date=2018-07-22&amp;rft.aulast=Basham&amp;rft.aufirst=Marc&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fidahostatejournal.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Feast-idaho-confederate-flag-display-creates-controversy%2Farticle_659c7ac7-37c1-5ad9-a996-a243868b3207.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFlaggers+%28Confederate+flag+erectors%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-ignore-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-ignore_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Renkl, Margaret (January 29, 2018). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.